rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML941/msitem/p2_i10"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/msitem"/><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/sdc/ontology#UniCont"/><dcterms:hasPart>Diagram of the fraction of the eucharistic bread.</dcterms:hasPart><crm:P57_has_number_of_parts rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</crm:P57_has_number_of_parts><betmas:hasLocus><betmas:Locus><betmas:locusTarget/></betmas:Locus></betmas:hasLocus></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML941/msitem/p2_i11"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/msitem"/><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/sdc/ontology#UniCont"/><dcterms:hasPart>Brief treatise on computus, indicating the different cycles used and exemplifying them in calculating the movable feasts and fasts of 7400 A.M/ 1900 E.C. (= 1907-8 /A.D.).</dcterms:hasPart><crm:P57_has_number_of_parts rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</crm:P57_has_number_of_parts><betmas:hasLocus><betmas:Locus><betmas:locusFrom/><betmas:locusTo/></betmas:Locus></betmas:hasLocus></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML941/msitem/p2_i12"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/msitem"/><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/sdc/ontology#UniCont"/><dcterms:hasPart>Note , that the year [19]41 was 567 years after the death of St. Gabra Manfas Qeddus.</dcterms:hasPart><crm:P57_has_number_of_parts rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</crm:P57_has_number_of_parts><betmas:hasLocus><betmas:Locus><betmas:locusTarget/></betmas:Locus></betmas:hasLocus></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML941/msitem/p2_i13"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/msitem"/><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/sdc/ontology#UniCont"/><dcterms:hasPart>Note , that the 8000 years began 126 years after the death of St. Gabra Manfas Qeddus.</dcterms:hasPart><crm:P57_has_number_of_parts rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</crm:P57_has_number_of_parts><betmas:hasLocus><betmas:Locus><betmas:locusTarget/></betmas:Locus></betmas:hasLocus></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML941/msitem/p2_i14"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/msitem"/><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/sdc/ontology#UniCont"/><dcterms:hasPart>Note, that Wasanē was born on the feast of God the Father in Sanē, the same day that Rās Dārgē set out to conquer Arusi, and that in 1919 E.C. (= 1926-7 A.D.) she is 41 years, 2 months and 18 days old.</dcterms:hasPart><crm:P57_has_number_of_parts rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</crm:P57_has_number_of_parts><betmas:hasLocus><betmas:Locus><betmas:locusTarget/></betmas:Locus></betmas:hasLocus></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML941/layout/layout1"><dcterms:isPartOf rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML941"/><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/layout"/><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://w3id.org/sdc/ontology#UniMeP"/></rdf:Description></rdf:RDF>